[normal]e or because of exclusions will impact 
[normal]on learning and subsequently on attainment. Excl
[normal]usi
[normal]ons data for the White g
[normal]roup of which 
[normal]White British is a large subset shows that generally this group is more likely to be excluded from school than other 
[normal]ethnicities. 
[normal]2012 to
[normal] 2013 data shows 
[normal]that, of
[normal] the population of pupils excluded from school, b
[normal]oys
[normal] 
[normal]are more likely to be excluded whatever the 
[normal]ethnicity and
[normal] White female FSM have higher numbers of exclusions when compared to all other ethnicities’ cumulative 
[normal]dat
[normal]a.
